reviews.review_text:
This is THE version! Cleanest version I've ever heard, by far. Everything is so absolutely crystal clear, I almost miss the old crackles and pops of the more familiar versions. Almost. I've always liked this show alot, but felt that it wasn't quite on the level of some of their September shows, most notably 9/17 and 9/21. Over the years it's made it's way out of my rotation, but now I have a newfound appreciation for it with this new version, so I may have to reconsider my stance.

Dark Star here I come!

THE BEST SBD FOR THIS SHOW After sampling all of the different sources for this show, covering many different songs, my ears have determined that this Seth Kaplan tape is the absolute best available. Instrument levels and overall sonic balance is much improved, along with clearer, cleaner vocals. EQ can be slightly improved by listening though iTunes on the "Rock" EQ setting, but I prefer this tape straight up. 

Incredible show, maybe top 10 from the band's 35 year career. My favorite Dark Star of all time.

Wowzers You guys weren't kidding.  This show is outstanding in almost every way.  And I just moved to Oregon so that's kinda cool:)  Jerry's guitar sound and playing is really crisp and the interplay between him and Bob is amazing.  

I can't believe the quality of the sound.  Somebody has given that tape a lot of TLC over the years for it to still sound like that.  Amazing!!

redick head them playing samples on the sirius GD station this morning and am i glad i did.  Listed to it twice today.  By far my favorite Greatest Story Ever Told i have ever heard.  Changed the song for me.
